{
  "text": "Cell lysates were prepared as previously described [CITATION_1] . The lysates were then incubated with the indicated antibodies for 1 h at 4\u02daC. The immune complexes were precipitated with protein A/G agarose (Santa Cruz Biotechnology, Inc., Santa Cruz, CA, USA) for 1 h at 4\u02daC, washed extensively with lysis buffer, resolved in 4-20% gradient SDS-PAGE, and analyzed by immunoblotting. All immunoblots were developed by enhanced chemiluminesence (Amersham Pharmacia Biotech, Inc., Piscataway, NJ, USA).",
